    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-14T03:13:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-14T03:13:00-05:00" n="272"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d272">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2025</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vladivostok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-14T17:00:00+08:47">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 6 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Yesterday executive committee Soviet called upon American, British, Japanese
                    consuls in order named, for no apparent definite purpose, apparently to
                    cultivate friendly relations against time of need. They are now in full control
                    here, but strength decreasing and gathering of troops on Chinese frontier near
                    here causing uneasiness.</p>
                <p>They inquired from each consul, as though merely incidental to their visit,
                    whether notice has been received that consuls may send code telegrams, stating
                    to me notice has been sent Consul General of Japan for communication other
                    consuls two weeks ago. Japanese deny receiving such notice. Official written
                    notice promised to me to-day not yet received.</p>
                <p>Tokyo, Peking informed</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJK1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
